    <text type="letter">
        <body>
            <pb xml:id="leaf001r" facs="loc_jm.00304.jpg" type="recto"/> 
            <opener>
                <dateline> 
                    <name type="place"><handShift rend="printed"/>Medical Superintendent's</name>
                    <name type="place">Office.</name> 
                    <name type="place">INSANE ASYLUM</name>
                    <name type="place">LONDON ONTARIO<ptr target="loc.08174_n1"/></name>
                    <date when="1891-09-20"><handShift rend="manuscript"/>20 Sept <handShift rend="printed"/>18<handShift rend="manuscript"/>91</date>
                </dateline>
            </opener>
            <p>One more good day! Warm, bright, full of beauty and cheer! Thanks for "Literary World" with the notice (a good one)<ptr target="loc.08174_n2"/> of "Goodbye."<ptr target="loc.07894_n2"/>
                I have sent Horace<ptr target="n4267"/> a bundle of Photo's of myself all taken by D<hi rend="underline">r</hi> Johnston<ptr target="n4102"/> at Bolton&#8212;some groups<ptr target="loc.08174_n3"/> &#38;
                some just Wallace<ptr target="n6121"/> &#38; self&#8212;all (I think) good. We are having a good time here,<ptr target="loc.08173_n7"/> good talks, good drives, good <hi rend="underline">meals</hi>&#8212;lots
                of <hi rend="underline">splendid</hi> vegetables and fruits, <hi rend="underline">corn tomatoes</hi>, very fine <hi rend="underline">potatoes</hi>,
                <hi rend="underline">melons</hi>, <hi rend="underline">pears</hi> and all the rest of it. Tell Horace to give you that <hi rend="underline">Bolton Speech</hi>
                of mine to read and tell me what you think about it!</p> 
            <closer> 
                <salute>So long, dear Walt</salute>  
                <signed>R M Bucke</signed>
            </closer>
